 see the full changelog of Dokan plugin version 1.4: [new] Added admin&#8230;\n<p class=\"read-more\"><a class=\"btn\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/35273/dokan-plugin-version-1-4-released/\">Read More &#8594;</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/35273/dokan-plugin-version-1-4-released/\">Dokan Plugin Version 1.4 Released with New Features and Bug Fixes</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com\">weDevs</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"Aminul Islam Sajib\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1287:\"<p>A new update has been released for e-commerce plugin for WordPress, Dokan. The new version 1.4 brings a handful of new improvements, features and bug fixes.</p>\n<p>You can see the full changelog of Dokan plugin version 1.4:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[new] Added admin option to change store URL</li>\n<li>[new] Added withdraw threshold feature</li>\n<li>[new] Order report Export and listing</li>\n<li>[new] Added admin option to enable-disable store sidebar from theme</li>\n<li>[new] Coupon fee shipping removed</li>\n<li>[fix] Pagination compatible with WordPress v4.1</li>\n<li>[fix] Language translation fixed</li>\n<li>[fix] Seller name changed to store name at featured seller widget</li>\n<li>[fix] Fix product stock quantity save error</li>\n<li>[fix] Fix product variation stock error</li>\n<li>[fix] Settings page error fix</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Dokan plugin users should be able to update the plugin from WordPress dashboard. If you aren&#8217;t seeing notification for new update of Dokan plugin, make sure that you have entered your Dokan license key.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/35273/dokan-plugin-version-1-4-released/\">Dokan Plugin Version 1.4 Released with New Features and Bug Fixes</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com\">weDevs</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"https://wedevs.com/35273/dokan-plugin-version-1-4-released/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"Things you need to know before having a multi vendor eCommerce website\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"https://wedevs.com/34157/how-to-build-a-multi-vendor-ecommerce-website/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"https://wedevs.com/34157/how-to-build-a-multi-vendor-ecommerce-website/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 15 Jan 2015 07:08:30 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Dokan\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Tips and Tricks\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"dokan\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"E-Commerce\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"http://wedevs.com/?p=34157\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:655:\"<p>Not every eCommerce endeavor is a successful one. Internet is filled with shopping carts that are still trying to find their feat but the ground beneath them is either slippery, or shrinking fast enough. Does that means such merchants should&#8230;\n<p class=\"read-more\"><a class=\"btn\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/34157/how-to-build-a-multi-vendor-ecommerce-website/\">Read More &#8594;</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/34157/how-to-build-a-multi-vendor-ecommerce-website/\">Things you need to know before having a multi vendor eCommerce website</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com\">weDevs</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Sarah Parker\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6612:\"<p>Not every eCommerce endeavor is a successful one. Internet is filled with shopping carts that are still trying to find their feat but the ground beneath them is either slippery, or shrinking fast enough. Does that means such merchants should abandon eCommerce? Definitely not.</p>\n<p>Here is a guide for you to know how to build a multi vendor eCommerce website &#8211;</p>\n<p>The multi vendor eCommerce websites have come along as a great ray of hope for businesses struggling to find a reckoning. When you have exhausted your best and most valuable resources, spent quite a lot of money and the results are still not showing up, why not try your luck with multi vendor eCommerce setup?</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Image1.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-34172 size-large\" src=\"https://i2.wp.com/wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Image1-e1421305276603-1024x345.png?resize=1024%2C345\" alt=\"Image1\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" /></a><span id=\"more-34157\"></span></p>\n<h2>What is Multi Vendor eCommerce Website</h2>\n<p>As the name suggests, the multi-vendor setup allows multiple merchants to register with the same eCommerce website and add to the repository its own line of products, displaying the same in different sections. So, you have a single website where there is a union of fashion products, electronic gadgets, books, and so on – depending on the range of merchants running their business from the site.</p>\n<p>The biggest and apparently the most obvious benefit of this arrangement is that a website that caters to such diverse tastes draws large amounts of traffic. When you are selling products for a target audience across all breadths, the footfalls will most naturally be greater in number. And that&#8217;s what it boils down to at the end of the day.</p>\n<p>The prime reason for this trend getting trendier is the fact that more and more buyers are resorting to the Internet to buy stuff. So while they are on a website buying their favorite jeans, they would prefer clicking on a menu on the same site to look for a branded headphone rather than restlessly roaming around Google to get look for a separate website. The multi vendor websites thus serve a greater purpose.</p>\n<p>The success on the Internet ambit depends most on the user-friendliness metric. And when it comes to eCommerce, the user friendliness is addressed in a deep-rooted manner. You are offering your customers everything under one roof, and that is singularly the best reason for them to stick around.</p>\n<p>Now, if you are one of those multi vendors who is experiencing a solid slant towards building an online store with other vendors, Dokan is a multivendor e-Commerce solution that truly makes a sweeping difference.</p>\n<p class=\"western\" lang=\"en-US\" align=\"justify\"><a href=\"https://i2.wp.com/wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Image2.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-34173\" src=\"https://i1.wp.com/wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Image2-1024x451.png?resize=1024%2C451\" alt=\"Image2\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" /></a></p>\n<h2>Dokan – The &#8216;What&#8217; and &#8216;Why&#8217; Behind it</h2>\n<p>Based on WooCommerce, Dokan is a high-power eCommerce solution that contains the best of WooCommerce as well as WordPress.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>It is essentially a plugin with an integrated theme and it does provide you with a lot of flexibility to be inventive with its usage.</li>\n<li>As a vendor, you have a free rein to setup your own store in the shortest possible turnaround time using Dokan.</li>\n<li>It happens to boast of a really simple user interface that makes it a straightforward procedure to set up your store and integrate the most desirable and efficiency-driven features.</li>\n<li>When you have multiple vendors on a site, each of them has a separate dashboard. The dashboards again happen to be highly structured for a fuss-free usage and organization of the website by the site admins. Through these admin-friendly dashboard, the standard tasks of an online store like managing the product inventory, setting the prices and discounts, offering coupons etc. can be easily handled and executed.</li>\n<li>The provision for comprehensive and clear-eyed sales reports further makes Dokan a highly recommended eCommerce solution.</li>\n<li>Apart from the dashboard, every admin has a separate page for them that can be used for the branding purposes so that they have their own identity on a website that represents n number of brands.</li>\n<li>Dokan also has the provision for the store owners to have a structured way of managing the product reviews, just like a WordPress site admin manages the comments on their site.</li>\n<li>The procedures of shipping and billing also have a sense of structure to them, right from the time orders are marked to when they are processed, and finally when they are dispatched.</li>\n<li>At any point in time when you wish to terminate a merchant&#8217;s account from the website, you can simply deactivate them. At the same time, the reliable merchants can be marked as the &#8216;trusted sellers&#8217; for their effective promotion.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>What Takes Dokan Up and Beyond is its Matchless Customer Support</h2>\n<p>Be it your Android phone, an Internet connection at your home, or your CMS, if there is not a good support service that can resolve your issues or handle your queries, that has a huge impact on the overall quality of the product/service.</p>\n<p>In this regard again, the company that sells Dokan and offer some exceptional after-sale service to the customers. Being a new product in the circle, there are some characteristic issues that the users experience and need help with. The support department of such companies make sure that every issue is addressed promptly and in the most accurate manner. Whether you have a doubt regarding image upload, or subscription questions, registration problems and so on, you can find the answers for all.</p>\n<p>Now, when you are out there buying Dokan, you are welcomed by a number of options in terms of the payment plans you can sign up with. Companies can offer you a plan that allows a maximum of 5 sites, or a plan that allows unlimited sites installation.</p>\n<p>With multi vendor eCommerce websites being the flavor of the season, Dokan adds even more spice to it.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/34157/how-to-build-a-multi-vendor-ecommerce-website/\">Things you need to know before having a multi vendor eCommerce website</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com\">weDevs</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"https://wedevs.com/34157/how-to-build-a-multi-vendor-ecommerce-website/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"10 Differences Between WooCommerce Product Vendor and Dokan\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"https://wedevs.com/30625/best-woocommerce-multivendor-plugin/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"https://wedevs.com/30625/best-woocommerce-multivendor-plugin/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 17 Dec 2014 15:32:38 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:8:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Dokan\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"dokan\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"multilangiage\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"multiseller\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Multivendor\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"wc vendor\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"WooCommerce\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"http://wedevs.com/?p=30625\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:661:\"<p>If you start talking about Dokan, the first thing that makes it unique from other e-commerce solutions is its multi-vendor support. Dokan allows you to quickly build an e-commerce system based on WooCommerce that supports multi-vendor product sales. This means you can create&#8230;\n<p class=\"read-more\"><a class=\"btn\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/30625/best-woocommerce-multivendor-plugin/\">Read More &#8594;</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/30625/best-woocommerce-multivendor-plugin/\">10 Differences Between WooCommerce Product Vendor and Dokan</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com\">weDevs</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"Aminul Islam Sajib\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12159:\"<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-31695\" src=\"https://i2.wp.com/wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/dokanvswoocommerce.jpg?resize=692%2C198\" alt=\"dokan vs product vendors\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" /></p>\n<p>If you start talking about <a href=\"http://wedevs.com/theme/dokan/\" target=\"_blank\">Dokan</a>, the first thing that makes it unique from other e-commerce solutions is its multi-vendor support. Dokan allows you to quickly build an e-commerce system based on WooCommerce that supports multi-vendor product sales. This means you can create a marketplace and start earning by providing other sellers a place to sell items.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s natural for you to start comparing Dokan with other similar solutions. And the first thing that comes to anyone&#8217;s mind would be Product Vendors by WooCommerce. So let&#8217;s take a look at 10 differences between WooCommerce Product Vendor and Dokan multi-vendor e-commerce plugin.<span id=\"more-30625\"></span></p>\n<h2>1. Front-end vs Back-end</h2>\n<p>Product Vendor by WooCommerce works on the back-end of your site. Just like the WooCommerce plugin itself, the entire operation of Product Vendor is done on the back-end of WordPress. Starting from adding products, editing products, managing sales, monitoring reports, etc everything is done on WordPress dashboard if you use Product Vendors.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_31704\" style=\"width: 1034px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-31704\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/dokandashboard-1024x502.png?resize=1024%2C502\" alt=\"dokan dashboard\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Dokan brings every functionality of a full-featured e-commerce marketplace to the front-end of your site.</p></div>\n<p>But Dokan brings everything on the front-end of your site. That means you will only need to do the initial setup and configuration from the back-end of your site. Your sellers will almost never need to go to the back-end. Dokan is developed in a way that lets your sellers sell their products, set up their shop and add/edit products and their info right from the front-end of your site.</p>\n<p>So, if you like to keep your sellers on the front-end of your site, Dokan is the way to go.</p>\n<h2>2. Professional-looking store pages</h2>\n<p>Product Vendor adds a vendor as a tag. Just like you manage tags on your site, Product Vendor lets you add vendors and assign products to those vendors, so that they show up as products from that particular seller/vendor. This is the same as adding a tag and filing posts under that tag. It is not a very professional way of adding products under multiple vendors in a marketplace.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-31700\" src=\"https://i2.wp.com/wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/store-1024x301.png?resize=1024%2C301\" alt=\"dokan store page\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" /></p>\n<p>To see all the products from a particular vendor, Product Vendor displays all the products from that vendor in a single page. Basically, that&#8217;s the &#8220;store&#8221; of that vendor. And technically, that&#8217;s the &#8220;tag&#8221; archive.</p>\n<p>On the other hand, Dokan allows for all sellers to act as individual users. Sellers need to register on your site before they can start adding products. You can choose to manually approve every user&#8217;s ability to sell products or you can set it to auto-publish. Best of all is every seller on your site gets a wonderful personalized store page which has their contact information, map, personalized cover photo and a lot more.</p>\n<h2>3. Product Management by Seller or Admin</h2>\n<div id=\"attachment_31702\" style=\"width: 728px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-31702\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/dokanproductadd.png?resize=718%2C433\" alt=\"dokan product add\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Adding products using Dokan is easy and done on the front-end.</p></div>\n<p>Product Vendor plugin requires you &#8212; the admin &#8212; to add all products and then assign those products to the vendors. However, Dokan gives you the flexibility to let your shoppers add and edit products at their will. You can still add products manually and assign them to sellers, but if you want to, you can also let your sellers take care of that.</p>\n<h2>4. Different by Design</h2>\n<p>Product Vendors does not have any specific design or style associated with it. It just adds a vendor option to the product creation page and an ability to show products from a particular vendor.</p>\n<p>However, Dokan gives you the full flexibility to create/register sellers, give them permission to add/edit their own products, and have their own store page. The store page lists seller&#8217;s contact information, map, contact form, a cover image much like a Facebook page, and all of their products.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_31703\" style=\"width: 841px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-31703\" src=\"https://i2.wp.com/wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/sellerdashboard.png?resize=831%2C406\" alt=\"seller dashboard dokan\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Seller Dashboard on Dokan gives access to all information for the logged in seller.</p></div>\n<p>Moreover, because Dokan allows full front-end operation for sellers, it comes with a Seller Dashboard. It adds a dashboard consisting of reports, all orders, products, seller profile and other settings right at the front-end of your site. So your seller will have a great layout for managing their products, information and other settings.</p>\n<h2>5. Graphical Reports for Sellers</h2>\n<p>Product Vendor requires you to create a custom page to let your vendors see a graphical report of all sales made in the current month and earlier. Dokan, on the other hand, has a built-in reporting tab in Seller Dashboard. The dashboard, like the rest of the Dokan, is accessed from the front-end of your site. So your sellers can see their reports and get an idea of how their products are doing without leaving the front-section of your site.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/wedevs.com/static/landing/dokan//features/reports@2x.png?resize=1100%2C540\" alt=\"reports\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" /></p>\n<p>The Reports tab of Dokan&#8217;s Seller Dashboard shows total amount of sales, average daily sales, number of order placed, number of items purchased, amount charged for shipping, and a graphical chart showing number of items sold and number of orders received.</p>\n<p>You can also filter these reports by Top Sellers, Top Earners, Sales by Day and sort the search by a &#8220;from and to&#8221; date.</p>\n<h2>6. Order Email Notification for Everyone</h2>\n<p>Product Vendors does not have a built-in option to send email notification to your vendors as soon as an order is placed. An email is sent to the administrator of the site, but not to the vendor of the product. But Dokan will not need any additional plugin for this feature. Right off the bat, Dokan can send email notification to both the admin and the seller of the product as soon as an order is placed. So, by using Dokan, you eliminate the need for an extension just for receiving email notification, which can be crucial for the success of your business.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i1.wp.com/wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/mailtemplate.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-32478 \" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/mailtemplate-220x300.png?resize=379%2C516\" alt=\"mailtemplate\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" /></a></p>\n<h2>7. Media Library Security</h2>\n<p>Media library is where all of your images and other assets such as downloadable products are uploaded. By default, when you use just WooCommerce, anyone registered with the same website who has a role of Author or above can see media files uploaded by others. However, when Dokan is activated, it puts a restriction on who can see the media libary. This way, despite the fact that your sellers will be registered on your site, they won&#8217;t be able to see files uploaded by you or other sellers. They will only see the assets they themselves have uploaded.</p>\n<h2>8. Payment Withdrawal for Sellers</h2>\n<p>When using Product Vendors, you need to export a CSV and then import into PayPal to make payment to your sellers. You cannot control how much a seller needs to earn in order to make a withdrawal.</p>\n<p>Dokan lets you set a minimum amount that&#8217;s required to make a withdrawal request. When your seller/vendor&#8217;s earning exceeds the minimum amount required to make a withdrawal, the seller can request for a withdrawal. You will then be able to release their payment. Product Vendors does not give you the flexibility to set a limit on seller withdrawals.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>9. Dokan Comes with Compatible Theme</h2>\n<p>Product Vendors or Dokan &#8212; whichever you run, you need WooCommerce plugin first. WooCommerce works on almost any theme, but it works better with a WooCommerce-compatible theme that are developed with emphasis on e-commerce store. Most professional WooCommerce-supported themes cost a lot. But with Dokan, you get a professional-looking, optimized theme for free.</p>\n<p>So if you use Product Vendor, you will still be in need of a supported theme. With Dokan, you&#8217;ve got that covered! Take a look at Dokan theme in action in the <a href=\"http://demo.wedevs.com/dokan\" target=\"_blank\">demo here</a>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/dokan-e-commerce.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-26931 size-medium\" src=\"https://i2.wp.com/wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/dokan-e-commerce-300x224.png?resize=300%2C224\" alt=\"dokan e-commerce theme\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" /></a></p>\n<h2>10. Developer Documentation</h2>\n<p>Dokan plugin is extremely developer friendly! You can build on Dokan, work with its code, and make changes according to your needs. And to help you make development adjustments, Dokan provides extensive developer documentation covering various actions, hooks, and filters. Check out the <a href=\"http://docs.wedevs.com/category/plugins/dokan-plugins/developer-documentation-dokan/\" target=\"_blank\">Dokan Development Documentation here</a>.</p>\n<h2>BONUS: Extend Functionality with Add-ons</h2>\n<p>To extend the functionality of Dokan&#8217;s built-in capabilities, you can choose from a number of optional add-ons. Here&#8217;s a brief overview of some of the Dokan add-ons that you may find useful down the line:</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://wedevs.com/plugin/dokan/subscriptions/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Dokan Subscription</strong></a>: In addition to earning commission from sales made by other sellers, you can charge your sellers just to publish their products on your platform. This is useful if your marketplace has grown big and if you only want serious sellers to sign up to sell on your shop.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://wedevs.com/plugin/dokan/per-product-shipping/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Per Product Shipping</strong></a>: Set a shipping criteria on a per product basis.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://wedevs.com/plugin/dokan/seller-vacation/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Seller Vacation</strong></a>: Allow your sellers to temporarily go offline (take vacation) and pause their products from the site. It will also show a customized message stating that the seller is temporarily unavailable for selling.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://wedevs.com/plugin/dokan/paypal-adaptive-payments/\" target=\"_blank\">PayPal Adaptive Payment</a>: Let your sellers receive their share of the payment at the same time as the customer makes the payment. This is useful when a customer shops products from multiple sellers at the same time.</p>\n<p>Check out <a href=\"http://wedevs.com/dokan-add-ons/\" target=\"_blank\">more add-ons for Dokan plugin here</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/30625/best-woocommerce-multivendor-plugin/\">10 Differences Between WooCommerce Product Vendor and Dokan</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com\">weDevs</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://wedevs.com/30625/best-woocommerce-multivendor-plugin/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n		